# CODEOWNERS — required reviewers for agent-surface paths.
#
# Why this exists: skills/ and .agents/ load into downstream agent sessions
# via `npx skills add`. A PR that modifies them affects every consumer.
# Pair this file with a branch-protection rule on main that requires:
#   - the `static-checks` CI job to pass
#   - at least one approving review from a code owner
#
# Replace @Thulr with the actual GitHub handle(s) of the people you want
# blocking merges on these paths. GitHub teams (e.g. @org/maintainers) work too.

# Default owner — catches anything not matched below.
*                                   @Thulr

# Skills bundle (loaded into downstream agent sessions).
/skills/                            @Thulr
/skills/.experimental/              @Thulr

# Repo-local agent surface (loaded into this repo's own agent sessions).
/.agents/                           @Thulr

# CI, workflow, and structural gates.
/.github/                           @Thulr
/Justfile                           @Thulr

# Public-facing documentation that shapes how downstream users install + use skills.
/README.md                          @Thulr
/THIRD_PARTY.md                     @Thulr
/LICENSE                            @Thulr
